Ukraine's opposition leader Viktor Yushchenko said Friday that he was not accusing the SBU secret services of trying to poison him despite suspicions that he ingested a massive dose of dioxin during a dinner with two of its agents.
The opposition leader declined to comment on assertions from several of his allies that Russian intelligence agencies had a hand in his poisoning in September, which kept him from the campaign trail and disfigured his face weeks before a first-round presidential election.
